hy there needs to be both planning reform and a more active role for the state, including local government.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHousing policyzEngland. 0aHousingxEnvironmental aspectszEngland. 0aHousing, RuralzEngland. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh1 aLloyd, Toby, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z9783111196664oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144733999140uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447346654?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447346654423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447346654/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2018